The principle of the real contracts is part performance: their causa civilis was the fact that one of the parties had done all that he had primarily undertaken. Shortly aster the fall os the Republic‚ and per- haps, as has been supposed, through the influence of the jurist Labeo (Dig. 15. 5. 1. 1 ; ib. 19. pr.; ib. 20. pr.), the Roman contract system received a considerable extension by a more general recognition of this principle.
